General Public Utilities Corpsaid the New Jersey Board of Public Utilities has approved a 72mln dlrs annual reduction in energy-adjustment charges for thecompany's Jersey Central Power and Light Co subsidiary.    The change in the utility's Levelized Energy AdjustmentCharge represents a five pct decrease in overall electricityrates.    On January 28, Jersey Central filed for a 32 mln dlr a yeardecrease in the charge, asking to retain the difference toprevent an increase in these charges next year, a companyspokesman said. Reuter&#3;